<h4>Read XML Data in the DES</h4>

<br />
<a href="wikka.php?wakka=DEReaderDef">DES</a> data is treated differently than TRE data. If you are reading this you may be trying to get SICD data out of the DESDATA section.  SICD (and other DES') takes advantage of the fact that the DES can be very large (~1GB).  That gives the program more than enough room to write out meta-data, etc.  Since this data can be very large, we parse the user-defined section of the DES (which would be empty in many DES (SICD included), and simply give the developer an <a class="missingpage" href="wikka.php?wakka=SegmentReaderDef%252Fedit" title="Create this page">API</a> for getting out the DES data.  This offers the developer two methods of handling the XML data.  The first is to treat it as a TRE explicitly and load it into a TRE object using the generic XMLTRE plugin for NITRO (which uses libxml2 underneath), and the second is to use our favorite XML parser to read it, by interfacing the NITRO DES API with an existing library (which could be SAX, DOM, pull, or even a data binding API).<br />
<br />
In our first example, we read the DESDATA right into a NITRO TRE object:<br />
<br />
<!--start GeSHi-->
<div class="code" style="font-family: monospace;">nitf_SegmentReader* deReader = nitf_Reader_newDEReader<span class="br0">&#40;</span>reader, <span class="nu0">0</span>, &amp;error<span class="br0">&#41;</span>;<br />
off_t length = nitf_SegmentReader_getSize<span class="br0">&#40;</span>deReader, &amp;error<span class="br0">&#41;</span>;<br />
nitf_TRE* sicdXML = nitf_TRE_construct<span class="br0">&#40;</span><span class="st0">&quot;XMLTRE&quot;</span>, <span class="st0">&quot;SICD_XML&quot;</span>, &amp;error<span class="br0">&#41;</span>; <span class="coMULTI">/* Note for 2.0 that length is removed */</span><br />
nitf_TRE_read<span class="br0">&#40;</span>sicdXML, deReader-&gt;inputHandle, record, &amp;error<span class="br0">&#41;</span>;<br />
<br />
<span class="coMULTI">/* Now we can query the TRE */</span></div>
<!--end GeSHi-->
